✅ 2) Basic Linux Commands (SUPER IMPORTANT)

Q6. How to check current directory?
pwd

Q7. List files and folders?
ls
ls -l
ls -a

Q8. Create folder and file?
mkdir test
touch a.txt

Q9. Move inside folder?
cd test   // go inside the folder
cd ..     // go one directory back
cd ~      // move directly to home directory
cd /      // move to root directory

Q10. Copy / Move / Rename?
cp a.txt b.txt
mv a.txt newname.txt                   // renames a file
mv file.txt /path/to/destination/     // moves file to another directory

Q11. Delete file/folder?
rm a.txt           // delete file
rm -r foldername   // delete folder

⚠️ QC Warning: rm -r is dangerous.


Q12. View file content?
cat file.txt
less file.txt    // read large file 
head file.txt
tail file.txt

Q13. Search inside file?
grep "error" app.log
grep -i "error" app.log

Q15. Check running processes?
ps       // show running processes on current terminal only
ps -ef   // show all running processes in system
top      // live process running



Q16. Check disk and memory?
df -h
free -h


Q17. Permissions in Linux? (Very common)

✅ Answer : Linux permissions control access to files:
r read - 4
w write  - 2
x execute - 1

Check:
ls -l

Change permissions:
chmod 755 script.sh
chmod +x script.sh
📌 chmod +x makes script executable.

chown - change ownership
chown raj rajfile.txt


Q18. What is sudo?

✅ Answer:
sudo runs command with admin privileges.
Example:
sudo apt update


Q19. Basic Utilities
echo - print text
echo "hello"

wc - word count
wc file.txt
wc -l file.txt   // line count

sort - sort content

uniq - remove duplicates


✅ 3) nano / vi basic (editing files)

QC sometimes asks “How to edit a file?”

nano file.txt
or
vi file.txt

