✅ 4) Shell Scripting Fundamentals (QC + Interview)

Q19. What is a shell script?
✅ Answer (Winning) : A shell script is a file containing Linux commands that runs automatically to automate tasks.
File example:
backup.sh
Run:
bash backup.sh

Q20. Basic shell script example
\#!/bin/bash
echo "Hello Raj"
date
📌 #!/bin/bash is called shebang. Shebang tells which shell to use:


Q21. Variables in shell scripting
name="Raj"
echo "My name is $name"

